## Data and privacy
We collect and store your data in accordance with our privacy policy. We do not share your information with third parties, except when necessary to deliver our services.

For example, sending an email requires us to share the recipient's address and message content with a third-party email provider. We only work with reputable providers and aim to share the minimum data required.

At any point, you can contact [info@belcoda.org](mailto:info@belcoda.org) to download a full copy of your data, or to request your workspace's data be deleted.

## Security
We take security seriously. Our infrastructure runs inside a virtual private network, with all data encrypted at rest and isolated from the public internet. We regularly review and improve our security practices. Full documentation is available on request.

That said, no system can be guaranteed 100% secure. While we take every reasonable measure to protect data stored in Belcoda, absolute security cannot be guaranteed. We encourage users to follow best practices and understand that Belcoda cannot accept liability for data loss or breaches.

If you have questions about our security practices or would like to discuss your specific needs, please contact [info@belcoda.org](mailto:info@belcoda.org).

